# Render side-effects. Any rmarkdown or quarto render of a .Rmd or .qmd
# produces a sibling <basename>_files/ directory of figure assets, and
# optionally a <basename>_cache/. These are render scratch space; they
# belong nowhere in git, regardless of where the render happened to run.
# Generic patterns first so a stray render at the package root, in
# data-raw/, or anywhere unexpected is also covered.

*_files/
*_cache/

# Existing tutorial-tree rules below are redundant under the generic
# patterns above; kept for clarity in case the generic ones are ever
# tightened.

inst/tutorials/*/*html
inst/tutorials/*/*_files/
inst/tutorials/*/*pdf

# Why do I need these?

tests/testthat/testthat-problems.rds
docs

inst/doc

**/.quarto
/doc/
/Meta/
